Source: duckbotos-brain
Section: ai
Priority: optional
Maintainer: DuckBotOS Team <duckets@duckbotos.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), git
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: duckbotos-brain
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: python3.12, python3.12-venv, git, curl,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: DuckBotOS AI brain — 4-tier RAG memory system for Hermes and OpenClaw
 Installs the DuckBot RAG + Memory System as a pre-configured default
 package in DuckBotOS. Provides:
 .
   • 4-tier CoALA memory: working, episodic, semantic, procedural
   • Hybrid retrieval: vector + BM25 + Reciprocal Rank Fusion
   • Entity graph with bi-temporal edges
   • FSRS-6 spaced repetition with self-tuning forgetting curve
   • Wing/Room/Drawer 2D memory palace (MemPalace-inspired)
   • AAAK corpus indexing (scan thousands of memories in <500 tokens)
   • Agent-driven skill pipeline → agentskills.io SKILL.md
   • MCP stdio server: 67 memory tools for OpenClaw and Hermes
 .
 Installed to: /opt/duckbotos/brain/
 MCP server started on-demand by the OpenClaw/Hermes MCP plugin.
 Embedding backend: LM Studio (local, zero API cost) — pre-configured
 with DuckBotOS defaults. Can override via /etc/duckbotos/brain.env.
 .
 This package is installed in ALL DuckBotOS modes (Hermes, OpenClaw, Both).
 LM Studio must be running for local embeddings; falls back to OpenAI
-compatible API endpoints.